    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter tonight\u2019s slate with significant lineup adjustments necessitated by the weather-related absences of **Yordan Alvarez**, **Trea Turner**, and **Kyle Schwarber**. In their stead, we are leaning heavily on **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (77.34) and **Junior Caminero** (76.33), who emerge as our top plays. **Pete Crow-Armstrong** benefits from an elite matchup against a struggling starter (7.83 xERA), where his elite speed profile provides the exact boost we prioritize to secure SBs. Meanwhile, **Junior Caminero** holds the highest raw efficiency score, anchored by a premium batting order position (Order #2) that should maximize his counting stat output against Williams.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Dillon Dingler** (33.08), who failed to clear our 40.0 floor. While his raw base projection looked promising, the collision of a difficult matchup against Ritchie (2.57 xERA) and an unfavorable platoon split pushed his effective score well below the required threshold, making him a clear sit in favor of the more stable **Gary Sanchez** (58.32). Further down the order, we are capitalizing on the aggressive base-running environment for **Hyeseong Kim** (62.33), who receives a +5% efficiency bump due to favorable wind conditions, helping to offset the lower batting order slot.\n\nRisk management remains a priority given the volatility of today\u2019s matchups. While **Colt Keith** (47.28) and **Caleb Durbin** (48.83) carry marginal scores, they are essentially locked in to preserve our game caps. Owners should monitor the status of **Carson Benge** (47.75) closely; despite his sub-50 score, he remains in the lineup to ensure we don't bleed plate appearances while our high-end talent sits idle due to the postponements. We are effectively playing for efficiency in the middle of the order today, relying on the speed-oriented upside of the back-end bats to stabilize our Roto category standing.",
